CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 22, 1969, pg. 7 reads: "Career Conference - The Crescent Elementary School's sixth graders participated in their first Career Conference recently, under the supervision of Mrs. Louise B. Smith, coordinator. The conference ran from Tuesday through Friday with outstanding persons from various business and professional fields serving as panelists...Second segment of photo: Horace Winchester, postal clerk; the Rev. George Fitch, AMEZ Church; Mrs. Louise B. Smith, program coordinator and elementary guidance counselor; Miss Sue Downs, Urban League, and Ron Smith, assistant program director of the Urban League -Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Horace Winchester, Rev. George Fitch, Louise B. Smith, Sue Downs, and Ron Smith, seated on stage in Crescent Elementary School for career conference
